[{"id":"FT548841","type":"longtextV2","stimulusHtml":"Both images shown are from the illuminated manuscript known as the <em>Tr√®s Riches Heures du Duc de Berry</em>.<br>\nCompare and contrast the two images to analyze how social class is portrayed <strong>and</strong> how this portrayal relates to the meaning of the manuscript as a whole.","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p><img alt=\"The top of the manuscript features the zodiac images for Capricorn and Aquarius in an arch. A second arch contains an illuminated comet above a horse drawn cart. Below the arches is a banquet of knights and courtiers. Behind them are armored knights with banners, presumably on their way to a crusade. At the center of the banquet table is a regal figure flanked by church members.\" height=\"595\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/cc35b9035fb7dc2f6e0857b19513e9fe/original.png\" width=\"400\" /></p>\n\n<p>LEFT</p>\n<img alt=\"A second illuminated page shows the same archway with Aquarius and Pices and a second archway with months and the gold comet or sun above a horse drawn wagon. Below is a country scene of a prosperous farm. Inside three people are warming themselves before a fire. Outside dozens of sheep are penned together. In the yard is a silo, barrels, a cart and kindling. In the mid ground is a man in the front yard, a man with a burro is passing by, heading toward a small village in the distance.\" height=\"622\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/media.academicmerit.com/23926ba0d7e86d644eee1f9de02246ff/original.png\" width=\"400\" />\n<p>RIGHT</p>\n"}]}]